snippet.textDisplay: Ali Sethi is a great singer but Strings/new music directors need to be bolder and experiment more. Other than a great singer singing a great song, it sounded as mediocre and bland as Indian coke studio. Don't make bare bone songs, add flavor to it. Refer to Rohail Hyatt. The more you listen to season 6 the more you appreciate his creativity and boldness. Even his first season was bolder than having just one singer sing one song with just tabla. Did the background singers play a part? Was there even an instrumental solo that stood out? Even Ali Sethi himself has more creativity than this "music director". Just listen to his "Chan Kithan". He didn't just sing it like a tota (parrot). He made the song his own with his own style and rendition.
